INSERT INTO `members` VALUES (1,'si@yoomee.com','si','olive123','Si','Wilkins',1,'','I am a Ruby on Rails developer for Yoomee, a great web development agency based in Sheffield, UK. I helped create this website.','2011-04-28 11:18:54','2011-06-09 15:03:59','2011/06/01/02_03_37_696_IMG_6807_1.jpg',0,0,'77.86.30.132','537473622',14265787,6,'web development skills, music and reflections.','5arWR0bjfN','siwilkins',NULL,'14265787-wOscQ26TiHpSVoMgSf2z5Pchxcb1zDy7CrvV0bfvU','PVCTD3txKuQpUEdVu6zqBkFStEbJNLsbplo31GfM',0,'bf6b078f-bd6d-4a6b-91fb-94daafdb0a22','942012b7-9f46-4563-a53a-037505bf5432','http://www.linkedin.com/pub/si-wilkins/19/291/a36',0,0),(2,'andy@yoomee.com','andy','olive123','Andy','Mayer',1,'Yoomee','I\'m the founder of <a href=\"http://www.yoomee.com\" target=\"_new\">Yoomee</a>. We create bespoke social networks, tools and apps for online communities using Agile/Lean principles. We\'re helping PICNIC build this website - starting with a simple beta, and then continuously improving based on feedback.\n\nAt Yoomee, we specialise in building social web technologies for social good. Typical projects involve creative ways of connecting people together online, solving specific problems that bring about positive social outcomes in the real-world. We work with nonprofit, social entrepreneurs, charity, third sector and advocacy groups to create bespoke custom social networking websites and social media tools.\n\nFeel free to get in touch if you have any questions about this site, or want to discuss developing a similar project. If you\'d like to find out more about what we do at <a href=\"http://www.yoomee.com\" target=\"_new\">Yoomee</a>, then please check out our website at <a href=\"http://www.yoomee.com\" target=\"_new\">yoomee.com</a>.\n\nWhen I am not doing Yoomee, then I am busy being a father, husband, petrolhead, Arduino and fencing fan - touché!','2011-04-28 06:18:54','2011-06-28 08:59:50','2011/05/05/06_35_05_970_IMG_0055.JPG',0,0,'77.86.30.132','747785309',14701791,71,'you and me together online; Yoomee','xldlPUCLQB','andymayer',NULL,'14701791-y62zfHeAiezSd5q65hwBlvYshYSI2K2V201baYbxM','taIv480Qt4PiwbMzkipQF7wh0FHPjLGwsbSPnY9GIg',0,NULL,NULL,'http://uk.linkedin.com/in/yoomee',0,0),(4,'rich@yoomee.com','rich','olive123','Rich','Wells',1,'','I\'m the lead designer at Yoomee, an agile web agency in the UK. I helped to create this site (which is still a work in progress so go easy on me!)','2011-04-28 10:18:54','2011-06-20 10:02:14','2011/05/20/10_04_12_815_lomo_0.06.53.09_.jpg',0,0,'77.86.30.132',NULL,14713297,25,'drawing skills, and a passion for creating engaging user experiences.',NULL,'richwells',NULL,'14713297-f3NvVY2pWUglJYpHVPcv259GqNOkKkPAmdTALk2RI','ugOUKbT7tkiIMpibyUMW39XHCSRtVzqIz9kI0Q0pxE',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(5,'ian@yoomee.com','ian','olive123','Ian','Mooney',1,'','I\'m a web developer from Sheffield. I work for a company called Yoomee and helped make this site awesome.','2011-04-28 09:18:54','2011-06-20 14:38:04',NULL,0,0,'77.86.30.132','61102010',19117562,12,'a lovely mop of ginger hair.','5OLA9xcrVI','ianmooney',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,'http://uk.linkedin.com/pub/ian-mooney/29/85a/aa9',0,0),(7,'matt@yoomee.com','matt','olive123','Matt','Atkins',1,'','Sheffield-based web developer, musician and tea-drinker.','2011-04-28 11:18:54','2011-06-09 15:03:43','2011/05/31/01_48_50_736_matt_squarebw.png',0,0,'77.86.30.132','286103766',18734348,10,'developer skillz','O05vUjvOun','matkins',NULL,'18734348-7wSsilt3HqI9B3RBbtRrrBa1EfPlmB59jltDBJck','Eqs1Nj6yuw8mygUBvFNtcI2X70AMeK7gSU7mcw',0,'3c6967ab-d743-407f-ae7b-1399fa313365','12018bb7-759c-4392-9ea3-32b2b40f53ac','http://www.linkedin.com/pub/matthew-atkins/15/a45/b39',0,0),(9,'stikker@waag.org','','PICNIC11','Marleen','Stikker',0,'PICNIC','In 2006 Marleen Stikker started, together with Bas Verhart (Media Republic) PICNIC, the Cross Media Week. PICNIC is an international event in the areas of creativity, media, technology, entertainment, art and science. Picnic has been described as ‘the growing up version of Burning Man, with posher venues and more dealmaking’.\r\n\r\nAs ‘mayor’ of the ‘Digital City’ (DDS) in Amsterdam, Marleen Stikker in 1993 developed the first European free gateway and virtual community on the internet. A place where many citizens, organizations, companies and publishers made their first steps on the electronic highway. DDS has been described by Manuel Castells in ‘The Internet Galaxy’ as the most influential practice where computer networks meets civil society.\r\n\r\nIn 1994 Stikker founded Waag Society, a medialab, developing creative technological applications for societal innovation. Waag Society makes e.g. mobile city games for the youth, develops storytables for the elderly and researches the possibilities for networked performances. The Creative Learning Lab focuses on new ways of education. Waag Society is also concerned with the social effects of the internet: new ways of distribution, copyright systems, civilian authorship and cross media developments. Therefore, Waag Society cooperates in Creative\r\nCommons Netherlands and broadcasts on the internet via KillerTV and informs on e-culture through Waag Society Magazine.\r\n\r\nTo facilitate creative entrepeneurs, Marleen Stikker initiated the Media Guild, an incubator for 30 creative starters in technology, established in the new cultural hotspot of Amsterdam, Pakhuis de Zwijger. A joint effort is Culture Grid, a Cultural Service Provider offering streaming and hosting facilities for producers of innovative broadband content.','2011-05-05 09:11:46','2011-06-09 15:24:52','2011/05/05/03_10_27_315_screen_capture_37.png',0,0,'195.169.148.4','',NULL,6,'you exciting technology applications and a sixth sense for what’s next.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(10,'Bas@mediarepublic.com','','PICNIC11','Bas','Verhart',0,'PICNIC','I\'m a co-founder of PICNIC as well as co-founder & CEO of Media Republic, a leading digital media and entertainment company based in Amsterdam.\r\n\r\nI\'m a passionate entrepreneur and always on the lookout for the next big idea. I\'m currently a board member at Trendwatching.com and Eccky.com, and am busy with a new project seeking innovation in education.\r\n\r\n','2011-05-05 09:11:46','2011-06-13 09:19:42','2011/05/05/03_21_07_218_screen_capture_38.png',0,0,NULL,'',NULL,10,'the spirit of entrepreneurship and killer guitar riffs.',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(11,'kitty@picnicnetwork.org','','kitty','Kitty','Leering',1,'PICNIC','I\'m the Program Director of PICNIC. \n\nI have been involved with PICNIC from the very start. I have been responsible for project management of the whole Festival in 2006 and 2007. In 2008 I got more involved with the programming of the Specials and the Labs. As of 2009 I have been responsible for all of the PICNIC Festival programming. \n\nIn addition I develop, program, give advise on and manage professional events on a freelance basis (DutchBlend). I mostly work on events that focus on the crossroads between creativity, (media)technology, business and governance. A few examples of events that I have been working on are SpinAwards, ICT Delta, Mediapark Jaarcongres, Dutch Bloggies and TEDxWomen (as a volunteer project manager). \n\nUntil 2005 I worked as the Event Director Benelux for IT-research firm IDC, building their regional event business from the ground up. At Media Plaza (1997-2002) I got acquainted with the world of internet, ICT and new media. ','2011-05-05 09:11:46','2011-06-28 15:30:56','2011/05/29/15_04_36_20_Kitty_PICNIC10.jpg',1,0,'80.56.102.25','100000000380345',6235172,59,'you urban future scenarios and gourmet cooking skills.','q6KCLDkLiM','KittyLeering',NULL,'6235172-anhrPj4l7QpqCusDyL75Pyz7bXqa4CAcIPFf1lrCaU','vbBbVdZGYIf5fyfTQgWJaacWAVPdZGrHzV5ReImFU',0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(12,'Annemarie@picnicnetwork.org','','PICNIC11','Annemarie','van Asselen',0,'PICNIC','I\'m the Director of Sponsoring & Partnerships at PICNIC.\r\n','2011-05-05 09:11:47','2011-06-10 18:35:26','2011/06/07/04_40_00_488_AK_reunie.jpg',0,0,'87.210.12.170','',NULL,7,'you a passion for building relationships and capturing memories on film.','qra3l8_JWB',NULL,'Director Sponsoring & Partnerships',NULL,NULL,0,'3f06ad25-e0c8-484f-b78d-00a89ed14697','f96bfa4e-d873-4add-b354-db4e4ce06396','http://www.linkedin.com/pub/annemarie-van-asselen/0/54b/baa',0,0),(16,'juha@non-fiction.nl','','PICNIC11','Juha','van ‘t Zelfde',0,'Viral Radio','As researcher, developer and radical user in the converging domains of art, heritage, network technology and urbanism, I work as a middleperson between those who invent the future and those who mind the past. With Michiel van Iersel I co-founded Non-fiction, an innovation agency reconfiguring popular engagement with public institutions for the 21st century. Non-fiction, based in Amsterdam, works with a.o. the Stedelijk Museum, Stadsherstel and the Royal Concertgebouw Orchestra.\n\nWith Ben Cerveny and James Burke I co-founded VURB, a European framework for policy and design research concerning urban computational systems. The VURB foundation, based in Amsterdam, provides direction and resources to a portfolio of projects investigating how our cultures might come to use networked digital resources to change the way we understand, build, and inhabit cities.\n\nLastly, I founded Viral Radio, a vehicle for the dissemination of electronic music. Viral Radio sets up site-specific performances for festivals and music venues in Europe, displaying new developments in computer music exploration and hyperrhythmic dance music. It has worked with a.o. Exit Festival, North Sea Jazz Festival and Bimhuis.','2011-05-05 09:14:54','2011-06-18 12:38:58','2011/05/24/03_13_31_380_screen_capture_2.png',0,0,'62.163.213.87','725890240',NULL,6,'some friends...',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(33,'todd@picnicnetwork.org','todd','hamper123','Todd','Savage',1,'Marketing Manager','I\'m the Marke