 analysis. The office is led by seven partners and employs a staff of around 230 of more than 35 nationalities. To accommodate a range of projects worldwide, OMA maintains offices in Rotterdam, New York, Beijing, and Hong Kong.\n\nSince 2005, OMA has tripled in size while maintaining strict creative standards. In 2007, Van der Chijs accepted the Jan Huygen van Linschoten Award, the business excellence award granted by of Dutch bank ABN AMRO, for OMA\'s successful entrance and maintenance in emerging markets such as China, and amongst others the United Arab Emirates.\n\nBefore joining OMA, Van der Chijs held various management positions at Schiphol Group - a leading international airport management company - in the Netherlands and the United States. Prior to joining Schiphol Group, he worked for financial institution ING for over 10 years, in the Netherlands and abroad.\n\nVan der Chijs is a member of the Dutch Trade Board, and the Economic Development Board of Rotterdam. He is also member of the Board of Trustees of the Netherlands National Historical Museum, as well as a member of the Supervisory Board of Kennisland (Knowledgeland), an independent think tank that aims to strengthen the Dutch cultural, intellectual and economic spheres. Early 2011, Van der Chijs became member of the Supervisory Board of RET, the main public transport operator in the Rotterdam metropolitan area.\nIn March 2011 Van der Chijs was appointed by the Dutch Ministry of Economic Affairs, Agriculture and Innovation to head a \'top team\' charged with exploring ways of stimulating innovation and entrepreneurship in the Netherlands. The team will focus on the creative industries, and consists of representatives from creative companies, research institutes and government. The key objective of the project, called To the Top – Towards a New Enterprise Policy, is to give entrepreneurs more scope for their activities and enable them to grow. The \'top team\' will generate recommendations to help creative companies compete on the world market and benefit from growing world trade.\n\nVan der Chijs holds a master degree in Law from the University of Amsterdam, and has followed extensive post-graduate education at the Amsterdam School of International Relations and at INSEAD, France.','2011-06-17 10:57:36','2011-06-23 09:32:25','2011/06/17/03_59_05_77_OMA_VvdC.jpg',0,0,NULL,'',NULL,6,'...',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1),(214,'toby.barnes@wearemudlark.com','','PICNIC11','Toby','Barnes',0,'','Principle, Mudlark\r\n\r\nI have been delivering digital products and services since 1995, working in many roles\r\nin media and the digital world through publishing, production and development. I have\r\nworked for a number of key industry leaders such as Emap, Virgin, MTV Networks, and\r\nTwo Way TV Games. I have worked with a number of global clients including Microsoft,\r\nSCEE, Electronic Arts, RSC, Channel 4 and Mattel. As a founding member of Virgin\r\nMedia’s Interactive Division, I helped launch Europe’s first commercial interactive TV\r\nservice. More recently I’ve been responsible for interactive content across mobile, broadband\r\nand narrowband for multiple MTV European channels.\r\n\r\nI’m currently one of the principals at the Mudlark Production Company: a multi-platform\r\nproduction company \"Making Life Playable\".\r\n\r\nI’m also Executive Producer on Chromaroma, Mudlark\'s first major self published project.\r\nThis online multiplayer game played out as you travel the city with your Oyster Card.\r\n\r\nI have spoken at a large number of international events such as Playful, SXSW, Games\r\nDeveloper Conference, and Interesting on playful design, cheating, cities, play and open data.\r\nFinally, I function as an advisor to the Greater London Authority and the Mayor of London on\r\na range of digital issues.','2011-06-17 11:08:21','2011-06-20 10:33:40','2011/06/17/04_08_55_997_hiRes_TonyBarnes.jpg',0,0,'217.137.165.75','',14094091,8,'you ever so slightly closer to the future. (probably with some swearing)','mQv4sOG32g','tobybarnes','Principle','14094091-5w4KHyTMWakwhqHOky4OhwAVJ5dCFofRbvacIT3Jz','KVj6mTqpuIwCX6LZX2PAeuYaALy9bRA0G9lPgGNVPs',1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(215,'peter@istrategylabs.com','','PeterPICNIC','Peter ','Corbett',0,'','CEO, iStrategyLab\r\n\r\nI’m the founder and CEO of iStrategyLabs – an interactive agency that develops creative solutions to clients’ challenges and brings them to life in the digital and physical world. I’m widely known for my creative marketing approaches coupled with a deep technical background, and a focus on civic innovation through community building.\r\n\r\nI have won multiple industry awards and accolades:\r\n  - 6 Addy’s for digital and experiential campaigns\r\n  - 2 Living Labs Global Innovation awards\r\n  - 1 Pioneer Institute Better Government Award\r\n  - Power 30 Under 30™ 2010\r\n  - Named Technology Advisor to DC Mayor Vince Gray’s transition team\r\n  - 3x named one of the most influential Washingtonians under 40 by WashingtonLife\r\n  - Named one of 100 Tech Titans by Washingtonian Magazine in 2010 and 2011\r\n  - Named one of 25 Doers, Dreamers and Drivers by Government Technology Magazine\r\n  - Won Great Washington DC Board of Trade’s “One To Watch” award for being “A rising entrepreneur who has a bright and sustainable future in Greater Washington”\r\n  - Organizer of the 1000+ monthly DC Tech Meet up\r\n\r\nIn Government 2.0 circles, I\'m widely known for co-creating Apps for Democracy with Vivek Kundra and DC’s Office of the CTO, and the Apps for the Army program for the US Army.\r\n\r\nMy focus on creating – rather than just talking about – smarter, better, faster, and cheaper ways of doing things have inspired initiatives in more than 25 countries around the world. iStrategyLabs is currently working on the Apps for the Army program for the US Army.\r\n\r\nI’m a highly sought after speaker on the topics of creativity, entrepreneurship, marketing, social media, Government 2.0, Civic Innovation, mobile and web application development for federal, state, local government and consumer use, application development contests, innovation contests, digital divide issues and crowdsourcing.\r\n\r\nYou can follow me on Twitter here: http://twitter.com/#!/corbett3000\r\n','2011-06-17 11:59:38','2011-06-27 02:45:58','2011/06/17/05_00_34_91_PeterCorbett_foto.jpg',0,0,'68.48.87.241','2602130',NULL,6,'...',NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(216,'eva@except.nl','','EvaPICNIC','Eva','Gladek',0,'','Director & Industrial Ecologist, Except Integrated Sustainability\n\nEva Gladek, a native of New York City, is an industrial ecologist passionate about sustainability. Her work integrates knowledge from across the natural and social sciences to develop innovative solutions in sectors as diverse as agriculture, electronics, and information management.\n\nEva began her scientific career as a molecular biologist, and continued on to work as a science journalist and television producer before developing her expertise in industrial ecology. She is an expert in technical environmental management techniques such as Life Cycle Assessment, Material Flow Analysis, and applying green design principles. \n\nSome of her recent projects include the conceptual development of Polydome, a high-yield greenhouse that functions like a natural ecosystem and offers the potential for net-zero impact food production. She also recently worked on optimizing the material flows in a social housing neighborhood in Rotterdam, developing guidelines for the production of greener chemicals for a large chemical manufacturer, and designing a financing platform for sustainable development. \n\nEva holds a Master’s in industrial environmental management from Yale University and a Bachelor’s in molecular biology from Amherst College. Since 2009, she has served as co-Director of Except Integrated Sustainability.','2011-06-17 12:21:01','2011-06-20 21:00:15','2011/06/17/05_22_56_368_Eva_Online.png',0,0,'89.250.179.24','',NULL,8,'kickass food-producing ecosystems. ',NULL,NULL,'Consultant & Project Manager, Except',NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(218,'mj@terreform.org','','MJPICNIC','Mitchell ','Joachim',0,'','Co-founder Planetary ONE and Terreform ONE\r\n\r\nI’m known as a leader in ecological design and urbanism. I’m a Co-Founder at Planetary ONE and Terreform ONE. I have earned a Ph.D. at Massachusetts Institute of Technology, MAUD Harvard University, M.Arch. Columbia University, and BPS SUNY at Buffalo with Honors. I’m an Associate Professor at NYU and was previously at Columbia University, Syracuse University, Parsons, The New School for Design, Washington University, and was appointed the Frank Gehry Chair at University of Toronto. \r\n\r\nFormerly, I worked as an architect at Gehry Partners, and Pei Cobb Freed. I have been awarded fellowships at TED 2011, Moshe Safdie Assoc., and Martin Society for Sustainability at MIT. I won the History Channel and Infiniti Excellence Award for City of the Future, and Time Magazine Best Invention of 2007, Compacted Car w/ MIT Smart Cities. My project, Fab Tree Hab, has been exhibited at MoMA and widely published. \r\n\r\nI was chosen by Wired magazine for \"The 2008 Smart List: 15 People the Next President Should Listen To\". Rolling Stone magazine also honored me in \"The 100 People Who Are Changing America\". In 2009 I was interviewed on the Colbert Report. Popular Science magazine has featured my work as a visionary for “The Future of the Environment” in 2010.\r\n','2011-06-17 14:52:36','2011-06-17 14:54:15','2011/06/17/07_53_42_671_Mitchell_Joachim_cropped.jpg',0,0,NULL,'',NULL,6,'...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(219,'omedvedik@gmail.com','','OliverPICNIC','Oliver','Medvedik',0,'','Co-Founder, Genspace\n\nCo-founder and Principal Investigator, Bioworks Institute\n\nI earned my Ph.D. from Harvard Medical School in the Biomedical and Biological Sciences program. As part of my doctoral work, I used single-celled budding yeast as a genetic system to map pathways that underlie the processes of aging in more complex organisms, such as humans. \n\nPrior to arriving in Boston in 1999 for my doctoral studies, I have lived most of my life in New York City. I received my bachelor\'s degree in biology from Hunter College, City University of New York, in 1998. Since graduating in 2006 from Harvard, I have worked as a biotech consultant and taught numerous undergraduate molecular biology courses at Harvard.  I am a co-founder of Genspace, a non-profit community biolab that is focused on teaching and developing synthetic biology projects. I am also the principal investigator and co-founder of the Bioworks Institute laboratory for art and biology in Brooklyn New York.','2011-06-17 15:00:11','2011-06-21 14:22:08','2011/06/17/08_01_17_498_omprofile.jpg',0,0,NULL,'',NULL,6,'...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(220,'kelly.ogilvie@gmail.com','','KellyPICNIC','Kelly','Ogilvie',0,'','CEO & President, Blue Marble Energy\r\n\r\nI have built up extensive planning, strategy and outreach experience from over a decade of work in politics and finance. Before founding Blue Marble, I worked with the Seattle Chamber of Commerce to promote business interests in Washington State. My work with Vulcan Inc. (founded by Microsoft co-founder Paul Allen) included marketing and strategy planning for capital and real estate market holdings. \r\n\r\nI have also served as a Deputy Director in former Mayor of Seattle Gregory Nickels\' Office. There I led my team to form and manage strategic partnerships for former Mayor Greg Nickels and his well-known environmental initiatives. I started my career in the former Washington State Governor’s Office of Gary Locke\'s Office where I coordinated outreach efforts for the governor.\r\n\r\nI currently serve on the Board of Directors at Seafair and on the External Advisory Board of Washington State University’s Center for Environmental Research, Education and Outreach. I’m also honored to have served as an advisor to the President’s Council of Advisors on Science and Technology (PCAST) on issues relating to Advanced Manufacturing.\r\n','2011-06-17 15:10:13','2011-06-21 09:30:10','2011/06/21/02_30_10_361_KellyOgilvie_officialFoto.jpg',0,0,NULL,'',NULL,6,'...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(221,'mark@letsheal.org','','MarkPICNIC','Mark','Woerde',0,'','Founder, Letsheal.org\r\nCo-founder & Strategy Director, LEMZ\r\n\r\nI’m the founder of Letsheal.org and writer of the book How Advertising Will Heal the World and Your Business. I’m also the co-founder and strategy director of the award-winning Dutch advertising agency LEMZ.\r\n\r\nLetsheal.org is an Amsterdam based independent non-profit organization aimed at providing insights in how to transform brands into meaningful prosocial brands. \r\n','2011-06-17 15:18:05','2011-06-17 15:19:08','2011/06/17/08_18_29_382_MarkWoerde.jpg',0,0,NULL,'',NULL,6,'...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(222,'drfriendly@gmail.com','','AaronPICNIC','Aaron','Wolf Baum',0,'','I am an artist, researcher, and programmer using biologically and culturally-inspired algorithms to create interactive, self-organizing visual & audio art systems. \r\n\r\nI program computers to create universes in which life-like, organic forms emerge spontaneously in live, sensual collaboration with the artist; I then create instrument systems with which I perform in collaboration with artificial image and sound life forms.\r\n\r\nThe self-organizing nature of the systems make it simple and intuitive to create a vast range of fascinating content. The beauty of the results arises from the aesthetic feedback loops between the artist and the system. The patterns emerge from the human-machine interplay and are unique to all the details of that play. \r\n\r\nPlaying the same art-game twice does obtain the same result; although it may have chaotic behavior, the system includes no random elements. The systems produce interesting content immediately, but as one learns the personalities of these life forms, it becomes possible to collaborate with a new sort of Alien. This is the essence of my art form -- transforming our relationship with technology and biology from mere control to enlightened symbiosis. \r\n','2011-06-17 15:24:54','2011-06-21 17:02:26','2011/06/17/08_25_17_627_AaronBaum.jpg',0,0,'99.8.225.191','',NULL,10,'live Spirulina culture, to inoculate the algae revolution!  And my buzzing, buzzing brain...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(223,'eric_rosenbaum@post.harvard.edu','','wheelsun54','Eric','Rosenbaum',0,'',NULL,'2011-06-17 15:39:27','2011-06-17 15:39:27',NULL,0,1,NULL,'5856',NULL,2,'...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(224,'paul@geosho.com','','leeds123','Paul','Sandham',0,'',NULL,'2011-06-17 16:02:20','2011-06-17 16:03:41',NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,6,'a packet of crisps, a map and some knitting',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(225,'quest@eim.ae','','rootmini15','Quraish','AHMED',0,'','Architect, LEED AP','2011-06-17 18:02:16','2011-06-17 18:09:06',NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,2,'A new synthesis of SOCIOnomy, ECOnomy & ECOlogy and a lot of GREEN Passion.','HN0c4ZIyPW',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'946db9dc-b55e-4300-abcc-4885cc9d7b9e','fd002f6d-8d4c-4fc6-bb76-e8104219b729','http://www.linkedin.com/pub/quraish-ahmed/2/27a/518',0,0),(226,'mypililove@hotmail.com','','rootyoyo5','小傑','方',0,'',NULL,'2011-06-18 16:22:05','2011-06-18 16:22:05',NULL,0,1,NULL,'100000264965068',NULL,2,'...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(227,'eric.endique@yahoo.com','','noonjune54','Eric','Endique',0,'',NULL,'2011-06-18 16:52:57','2011-06-18 16:52:57',NULL,0,1,NULL,'100000749789002',NULL,2,'...',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0),(228,'miler_10_9@hotmail.com','','bluepush89','Miller','Silva Menejes',0,'','miler\n','2011-06-19 04:36:58','2011-06-19 04:39:38',NULL,0,