play&rdquo; for the planet.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Slides of the session are available here.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Communication of climate trends is a difficult problem uniquely suited to designers: crafting clear messages of unfamiliar substances at unimaginable scales into recognizable and actionable news. Advances in data visualization, the embrace of social networks and mobile platforms coupled with virtual and augmented realities offer new opportunities to create a shared sign in the public square.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	And not just any public square....</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	TIMES SQUARE !</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Today HeadsUp! 2011 and PICNIC are thrilled to announce the participation</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	of Thomson Reuters in providing an extraordinary venue for the competition.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The winning entries to the HeadsUp! 2011 Design Challenge will be awarded display time on TS2, Times Square Squared, a Reuters / NASDAQ Alliance. TS2, comprising both the NASDAQ and Reuters displays commands over 19,000 square feet of digital signboards over 21 stories high. 1,5 million people a day passing through Times Square, looking up: What will you post there?</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	TS2 live webcam</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	September 2010 - LAUNCH</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	January 2011 - COMPETITION OPENS</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	MAY 2011 - FINALISTS CHOSEN</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	JUNE 2011 - DISPLAY TIME ON TS2</p>\r\n','2011-05-24 12:22:55','2011-05-24 12:22:55','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-05-24 12:21:00',0,19,0,'HeadsUp!'),(81,1,'PICNIC in Beta','','<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	We are currently in beta - which means we&#39;ve released our new online platform before it&#39;s finished.&nbsp;Why did we do that? The answer is simple. We want to get feedback from you, our community, during the development process rather than afterwards.</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	And we sincerely appreciate your constructive comments! Therefore we will raffle off 3 free PICNIC Festival Passe Partouts among the feedback submissions that we receive before July 1, 2011. So don&#39;t be shy and tell us what you think! Than we&#39;ll build our new online platform together.</p>\r\n','2011-05-27 15:35:50','2011-05-31 08:31:08','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-05-27 15:34:00',0,27,998,'Beta'),(89,4,'Scenes from 2010','<br />\r\n','<h3>\r\n	Whether you&#39;re a veteran or first-timer, dive into our visual archives documenting past PICNIC festivals to enjoy both images at <a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/crossmediaweek/sets/72157624988417397/\" target=\"_blank\">Flickr</a> and some of our <a href=\"http://www.vimeo.com/picnic\" target=\"_blank\">PICNIC speakers at Vimeo</a>.</h3>\r\n<h3>\r\n	&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<h3>\r\n	What did everyone bring to PICNIC &#39;10?</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/16245565</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Reinier de Graaf on&nbsp;Urban Paradigm Shifts</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/16107033</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Dennis Crowley, Foursquare founder, on Social Cities</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/17756354</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Aza Raskin on Redesigning Memories</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://www.vimeo.com/16729734</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>\r\n	Evan Ratliff of Wired Magazine on Vanishing in the Digital Age</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://vimeo.com/15732565</p>\r\n','2011-05-27 20:12:42','2011-06-16 15:23:12','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-05-27 20:12:00',0,6,100,'Scenes from 2010'),(91,15,'Out of town visitors',NULL,'<p>\r\n	PICNIC Festival attracts some of the world&#39;s most creative and innovative minds. We&#39;ve arranged special rates on airfare and hotels. Book one of the three festival hotels <a href=\"/travel-and-accommodations\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>before 1 July</strong></a> for special savings, including the brand-new Mint Hotel.</p>\r\n','2011-05-27 22:43:21','2011-06-16 08:29:08','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-05-27 22:43:21',0,29,0,'Hotel and travel info'),(93,15,'Early Bird registration is open!','','<p>\r\n	Yay! PICNIC Early Bird Registration is open. Make sure you profit from our spectacular early bird offer and <a href=\"/festival-registration\" target=\"_blank\">buy a ticket now</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This year&#39;s PICNIC Festival will take place between 14 and 16 September, of course in beautiful Amsterdam. We&#39;d love to welcome you, so join us.</p>\r\n','2011-05-27 23:20:12','2011-06-16 09:48:53','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 05:00:00',0,38,0,'Registration starts today'),(94,1,'Contributors',NULL,'<p>\r\n	We are proud to have so many creative minds in the PICNIC community that we can call our friends. Not only do they have great ideas to make PICNIC an even better and more beautiful platform, they also help us to realize all of our crazy plans. And we love them for that! Big time.&nbsp;</p>','2011-05-29 16:56:24','2011-06-01 12:01:19','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-05-29 16:56:00',0,NULL,4,''),(96,31,'Nationale Postcode Lotterij','','<p>\r\n	The <strong>Dutch Postcode Lottery</strong> (Nationale Postcode Loterij) is a charitable organization focused on supporting organizations working to create a more just and green world through fundraising and increasing public awareness with the help of a lottery.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	It&#39;s Holland&rsquo;s biggest and most popular charitable lottery and it supports 75 charity organizations UNICEF, Greenpeace, WWF, IUCN and the Clinton Foundation. In 2009, the lottery allocated 256 million euros to its beneficiaries.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong><a href=\"http://www.postcodeloterij.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.postcodeloterij.nl</a></strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<strong>Postcode Lottery Green Challenge 2011</strong></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Green Challenge 2011 calls on creative, innovative minds to come up with concrete solutions to fight climate change. Anyone with a good idea for a product or service that reduces greenhouse gas emissions in a consumer-friendly way and contributes to a sustainable lifestyle is welcome to take part. Together with PICNIC, the Dutch Postcode Lottery started this initiative in 2007. The winner receives 500,000 euro from the Postcode Lottery to execute their plan.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.greenchallenge.info\" target=\"_blank\">www.greenchallenge.info</a></p>','2011-06-01 09:19:32','2011-06-15 07:41:39','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 09:14:00',0,58,0,''),(97,31,'Vodafone','','<p>\r\n	<strong>Vodafone</strong> is one of the largest mobile communications companies in the Netherlands and is part of the Vodafone Group, the world&rsquo;s leading mobile telecommunications group. Vodafone Netherlands has a customer base of 4.4 million customers. It has a Head Offices in both Maastricht and Amsterdam. Almost 3000 employees work with Vodafone Netherlands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Vodafone is dedicated to providing the best products and services for the ever-innovative mobile telecoms market. Their goal is to provide the best accessibility and connectivity worldwide, for the best possible price. Their passionate and talented employees help keep Vodafone at the leading edge of their market.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information visit: <a href=\"http://www.vodafone.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.vodafone.nl</a></p>\r\n<h4>\r\n	Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	<em>With Vodafone Mobile Clicks we provide a stage for young innovative mobile internet start ups to accelerate their ideas and support them in making their next step in the mobile market.</em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Vodafone Mobile Clicks</strong> is an international contest to identify and develop the best, most innovative mobile internet start-ups. Announced at The Next Web Conference in Amsterdam, the closing date for entries is midnight CET on 12th June, 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Already known as the biggest start-up competition of its kind, this year&rsquo;s Vodafone Mobile Clicks is open to seven markets. Any start-up in Germany, the Netherlands, Portugal, the Republic of Ireland, Spain, Turkey or the United Kingdom that has a mobile site, service or application can compete for the <strong>&euro;225,000</strong> prize fund.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Judging will take place over three rounds. Firstly, each competing market will draw up a shortlist of their five best submissions, then a local winner will be selected. Lastly, all seven local winners will be invited to represent their country in a live final at the PICNIC festival in the Netherlands on 15th &ndash; 16th September 2011, where the overall winner will be chosen.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This year&rsquo;s <a href=\"https://developer.vodafone.com/mobileclicks2011/jury-bios/\" target=\"_blank\">high-profile judges</a> include Rudy de Waele, founder of Mobile 2.0 Europe and dotopen; Peter Barry, Head of VC and Start-up at Vodafone Ventures; Paul Jozefak, Managing Partner at Mobile VC; Reshma Sohoni, Partner at Seedcamp, and Lee Epting, Director of Content Services at Vodafone Group. Each judge will score entries based on five criteria:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Originality, creativity and innovativeness</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Technical and operational feasibility</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Economic and financial viability</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Value to end-users</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		The quality of the management team (e.g. their experience, knowledge, skills, relationships)</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is a fantastic opportunity to gain expert feedback for your entry, both qualitatively and quantitatively from all of the jury members. And if your entry reaches the finals, then you&rsquo;ll also benefit from our extensive PR and coverage.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you have the inspiration and desire to be the best, then <a href=\"https://id.developer.vodafone.com/user/signin/?next=/authenticate/%3Fopenid.claimed_id%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fspecs.openid.net%252Fauth%252F2.0%252Fidentifier_select%26openid.identity%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fspecs.openid.net%252Fauth%252F2.0%252Fidentifier_select%26openid.assoc_handle%3D%257BHMAC-SHA256%257D%257B4de5ec95%257D%257B%252F9pBdA%253D%253D%257D%26openid.return_to%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fsubmit.vodafonemobileclicks.com%252Fdesktopmodules%252Fauthenticationservices%252Fvodafoneopenid%252Fentrypage.aspx%253Fdnoa.userSuppliedIdentifier%253Dhttps%25253A%25252F%25252Fid.developer.vodafone.com%25252Fauthenticate%26openid.realm%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fsubmit.vodafonemobileclicks.com%252F%26openid.mode%3Dcheckid_setup%26openid.ns%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fspecs.openid.net%252Fauth%252F2.0%26openid.ns.alias3%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fopenid.net%252Fsrv%252Fax%252F1.0%26openid.alias3.required%3Dalias1%252Calias2%252Calias3%252Calias4%252Calias5%252Calias6%252Calias7%252Calias8%26openid.alias3.mode%3Dfetch_request%26openid.alias3.type.alias1%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcontact%252Femail%26openid.alias3.count.alias1%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias2%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%26openid.alias3.count.alias2%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias3%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%252Ffriendly%26openid.alias3.count.alias3%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias4%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%252Ffirst%26openid.alias3.count.alias4%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias5%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252FnamePerson%252Flast%26openid.alias3.count.alias5%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias6%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcontact%252Fphone%252Fdefault%26openid.alias3.count.alias6%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias7%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcompany%252Fname%26openid.alias3.count.alias7%3D1%26openid.alias3.type.alias8%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Faxschema.org%252Fcontact%252Fweb%252Fdefault%26openid.alias3.count.alias8%3D1\" target=\"_blank\">enter today!</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 10:17:46','2011-06-02 11:40:07','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 10:17:00',0,61,1,''),(98,32,'UPC',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<em>Our products are used to communicate, interact, be entertained, seek information, share content and help the consumer understand the world around them.</em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Cable and media firm <strong>UPC</strong> is one of the leading providers of television, broadband internet, and telephone services in the Netherlands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	UPC provides 2 million households with digital or analog television. As of 31 March 2010, UPC supplied 772,000 households with broadband internet and had 654,000 subscribers for digital telephone services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	UPC is a consolidated subsidiary of Liberty Global, Inc. (NASDAQ: LBTYA, LBTYB, LBTYK). Liberty Global delivers television, broadband internet and telephone services to 10 million customers in eleven European countries.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more info visit: <a href=\"http://www.upc.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.upc.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 10:50:34','2011-06-02 11:40:41','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 10:50:00',0,60,0,''),(99,32,'Chamber of Commerce','','<p>\r\n	The Dutch Chamber of Commerce (Kamer van Koophandel) manages the trade register of all businesses in the Netherlands. The Chamber of Commerce for Amsterdam, the regional representative organization for the private business sector, is the country&#39;s largest Chamber with over 200.000 companies on its register.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Chamber takes all steps within its power to maintain and stimulate the robust economic health of the Amsterdam region. The Chamber accumulated knowledge, contacts and partnerships makes it the essential reference point for every firm doing or seeking to do business in the Amsterdam region. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.kvk.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.kvk.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 10:58:59','2011-06-02 11:39:00','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 10:58:00',0,56,2,''),(100,32,'RTL',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>RTL Nederland</strong> is an all round media company and nationwide market leader with four television stations (RTL 4, RTL 5, RTL 7, RTL 8), the digital channel RTL Lounge and the number one Dutch radio station Radio 538.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	RTL Nederland entertains and informs a broad audience 24/7 on all relevant platforms. RTL Nederland&#39;s channels offer a wide variety of Dutch and foreign films, series and shows, including popular formats such as RTL Boulevard and RTL News. With its leadership in the Dutch television and radio markets and its expanding role in digital media with for example RTL.nl and RTL Gemist (TV shows online), RTL Nederland is one of Holland&#39;s leading media companies.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	RTL Nederland is a subsidiary company of RTL Group and part of the international Bertelsmann organization.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.rtlnederland.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.rtlnederland.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 11:07:23','2011-06-02 11:40:56','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 11:07:00',0,59,1,''),(101,32,'SII','','<p>\r\n	<em>SII is involved in a large number of service innovation projects which are of interest of people who want to be updated about the latest ICT developments in relation to cutting edge innovative services.</em></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The goal of the innovation program <strong>Service Innovation &amp; IC</strong>T (SII) is to make the Netherlands the European hub for content services and the European centre of excellence for financial logistics. The program SII has started by the Dutch ministry of Economic Affairs in January 2010 and the first phase of SII will run till end 2011. The government has provided a subsidy for the first phase of 12.5 million euro. The program consists of a number subprograms such as the Infrastructure Program, the TOP Program and the Tender Program. The SII office will also execute the subprogram Knowledge Dissemination and Value Acceleration.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The main subjects in the Tender Program are content, connectedness, e-lifestyle, e-invoicing and e-payments. SII focuses on service innovation realized by consortia of co-operating companies and institutions representing large companies, SME&rsquo;s en knowledge institutes. SII stimulates the growth o ecosystem that will secure the growth of the knowledge intensive service industry.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information visit: <a href=\"http://www.si-i.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.si-i.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 11:27:47','2011-06-02 11:42:11','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 11:27:00',0,62,7,''),(102,32,'Logica','','<p>\r\n	<strong>Logica</strong> is a leading IT and business services company.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Logica employs 40,000 people across 36 countries. The company provides business consulting, systems integration, and IT and business process outsourcing services.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Logica works closely with its customers to release their potential - enabling change that increases efficiency, accelerates growth and manages risk. The company applies its deep industry knowledge, technical excellence and global delivery expertise to help its customers build leadership positions in their markets. Logica is listed on both the London Stock Exchange and Euronext (Amsterdam) (LSE: LOG; Euronext: LOG).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.logica.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.logica.com</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-01 11:36:59','2011-06-02 11:41:14','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 11:36:00',0,57,4,''),(103,11,'Boilerplate','','<h3>\r\n	About PICNIC</h3>\r\n<p>\r\n	The PICNIC name represents everything we strive to be. It is a gathering of friends old and new, where everyone brings something to the table.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC is about innovative ideas for business, people and society. It is a platform that brings together people from diverse backgrounds who like to exchange ideas and insights and are keen to expose themselves to ideas outside their own area of expertise. PICNIC offers an online meeting place to do that through the PICNIC Club, our online community, and the PICNIC News Network (PNN) that offers inspiring, crowdsourced and co-hosted content.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition PICNIC also organizes off line events, culminating in our annual festival in Amsterdam. During three intensive days we mix creativity, science, technology, media and business to explore new solutions in the spirit of co-creation. Curious minds eager to exchange knowledge, ideas and skills gather at PICNIC and leave with a new perspective on what is possible.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more information, please contact:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Todd Savage, Marketing manager</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Tel: +31 (0)20 320 5813</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Todd@picnicnetwork.org</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Haarlemmerweg 321 B</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	1051 LG Amsterdam</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.picnicnetwork.org</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Twitter: @picnicfestival</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Facebook: PICNIC</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	#picnic11</p>\r\n','2011-06-01 12:19:20','2011-06-01 12:19:42','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-01 12:18:00',0,NULL,0,''),(104,15,'Last chance to submit for Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011!',NULL,'<p>\r\n	With only a few days to go before the Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011 competition closes, the race is on across the Mobile start-up community. Make sure to submit and maybe you&#39;ll win a share of the &euro;225,000 prize fund. The closing date for entries is midnight on Sunday, 12th June, 2011 CET, so no time to lose!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This year&rsquo;s panel of impressive local and global judges includes Rudy de Waele, founder of Mobile 2.0 Europe and dotopen; Peter Barry, Vodafone Ventures; Paul Jozefak, Mobile VC; Reshma Sohoni; partner at Seedcamp and Lee Epting, Vodafone Group. Each judge will be scoring entries based on five criteria: originality, creativity and innovation; technical and operational feasibility; economic and financial viability; value to end-users; and finally, the quality of the management team.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Budding start-ups looking for inspiration need look no further than last year&rsquo;s Vodafone Mobile Clicks winner, Cardmobili. Since winning the competition in September 2010, Portugal-based Cardmobili has launched its application on Windows Phone 7, translated the app into French and Spanish and also has seen its user base increase by 80%. Check out this short interview with Helena Leite, CEO of Cardmobili <a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/vodafone#p/u/0/UpCaYOx88QE\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This Sunday at midnight sharp, the registration period will close. Do not wait till the last minute, as it will take around 30 to 40 minutes to submit! And you do not want to be too late. So submit your entry now into the Vodafone Mobile Clicks 2011 competition at <a href=\"http://www.vodafonemobileclicks.com\" target=\"_blank\">www.vodafonemobileclicks.com</a>!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>','2011-06-08 11:07:44','2011-06-08 11:07:44','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-08 11:07:44',0,65,0,''),(106,15,'Sign up for The Marketplace by 4 July',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Are you a small company with an exciting new product or service that you want to introduce to thousands of leaders in the creative and business sectors? Then make sure to sign up for The Marketplace! Organized by the Chamber of Commerce and Syntens together with KansenKanon and Mediaguild, The Marketplace is taking place for the 6th time during the PICNIC Festival 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The theme of this year&#39;s PICNIC Festival&nbsp;is Urban Futures. The world is undergoing the largest wave of population growth in history: we are looking at more than 8 billion people in 2030 and essentially all of the growth will take place in the less developed countries, concentrated among the poorest populations in urban areas. By that time at least 70% of the world population will be living in an urban environment. This will have a huge impact on social interaction, government, infrastructure, sustainability and healthcare. Technology and design will play a leading role in developing potential solutions. <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/themes\" target=\"_blank\">Find out more about the theme</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Each day at the&nbsp;PICNIC Festival (14-16 September 2011), The Marketplace will give 25 different young companies the chance to present themselves and interact with the PICNIC audience.&nbsp;Each company will create their own stand in a unique, casual, fast-paced networking environment that looks like a marketplace - but with a PICNIC twist. Companies who have a clear connection to or passion for this year&#39;s theme are especially encouraged to apply.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If you&#39;re ready to meet inspiring people, share your ideas and get some great business leads, be sure to <strong>sign up for The Marketplace before 4 July</strong>. You can view more detailed information on the <a href=\"http://www.syntens.nl/Nieuwsberichten/Nieuws/6de-Marketplace-tijdens-Picnic-11.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Syntens website</a> (in Dutch) or send an email to <a href=\"mailto:brh@syntens.nl?subject=Marketplace%20at%20PICNIC\" target=\"_blank\">Bruni Hofman</a> at Syntens to register your company. Don&#39;t hestitate - this is an opportunity you don&#39;t want to miss.</p>\r\n','2011-06-09 15:26:18','2011-06-14 14:16:13','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-09 15:23:00',0,66,0,''),(107,21,'Club ground rules',NULL,'<p>\r\n	We want the Club to be an interesting community of people - from those who&rsquo;ve been sharing the PICNIC blanket for a number of years, and who&rsquo;ve helped to make it well worn, to those who&rsquo;ve only just heard about about PICNIC, and everybody in between.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The PICNIC Club is open to all, so you can:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			find other people who love to PICNIC and all it stands for</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			share ideas, ask questions and generally use people you can trust as a sounding board</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			have conversations about the many and diverse issues which interest you</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			inspire others with your passion, knowledge and experience.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>\r\n	The rules</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	We want the Club to be a fun place, which means everybody playing by the rules - which are simply;&nbsp;don&#39;t be boring.&nbsp;If you don&#39;t know what boring is, then you probably are. Here are some clues:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Boring people drone on and on about what they do when nobody has asked them or is interesed</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people post irrelevant links to commercial projects. Please don&#39;t use PICNIC to carry out your next marketing campaign or to advertise. If somebody is interested and wants to find out, they can ask you directly</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people spam those who&rsquo;ve chosen to share their PICNIC experience</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people hide behind fake online identities&nbsp;</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people don&#39;t use their real name online</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		<p>\r\n			Boring people don&#39;t keep their profiles up to date.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please don&#39;t spoil it for others. If you choose to be boring, then we reserve the right to lock you out of our PICNIC Club. Got it?</p>\r\n','2011-06-14 14:51:27','2011-06-16 14:28:51','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-14 14:51:27',0,NULL,0,'Ground rules'),(108,15,'Join PICNIC next week at Futur en Seine','','<p>\r\n	We&rsquo;re heading to France for upcoming Futur en Seine festival! Following the success of the 2009 edition, the <a href=\"http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Futur en Seine Festival</a> again takes hold of the city and region of Paris from 17th to 26th June. This is THE popular Festival of Life and Creativity, where the general public meets the innovative creative industries to imagine, build and celebrate the digital future together!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The incredibly rich and diverse festival program allows everyone --&nbsp;whether curious, passionate, amateur or professional -- to share one, common experience: to test new technology <em>in situ </em>and to create the digital future together around five central themes: The Future of Life, the Future of Music and Image, the Future of Creation, the Future of Communications and the Future of the City.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	At the very heart of the festival, a cycle of international conferences and workshops will be held over a period of six days in prestigious locations (Coll&egrave;ge de France, 104, Ga&icirc;t&eacute; Lyrique, Forum des Images et Ecole Normale Sup&eacute;rieure). Internationally renowned speakers have confirmed their participation, including Everyware author Adam Greenfield, FabLab inventor Neil Gershenfeld, McLuhan associate Derrick de Kerckhove, futurist and molecular biologist Jo&euml;l de Rosnay, educationalist Sugata Mitra, artists Maurice Benayoun and Yoichiro Kawaguchi, legendary pioneer of satellite communications, Candace Johnson, designer, architect and author Michael Shamiyeh, transportion innovator Robin Chase, SXSW Producer Shaw O&#39;Keefe, <strong>PICNIC co-founder Marleen Stikker</strong>, &quot;Internet of Things&quot; author Rob van Kranenburg and many more...</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The conference cycle will also include the second edition of the <a href=\"http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/fiche/874/\" target=\"_blank\">European Street Design Challenge</a>, which will culminate in the selection of the award winner during the Future of the City.&nbsp;<strong>PICNIC is coming with three teams (from Eindhoven, Amsterdam &amp; Rotterdam) to compete in the second edition of the European Street Design Challenge</strong>. This competition, first held at PICNIC &lsquo;10, brings together students, start-ups and SMEs for a three-day urban design challenge. At Futur en Seine the teams will battle to develop solutions that increase a sense of &ldquo;connectedness&rdquo; between historic Paris and its expanding suburbs.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For four days, the CentQuatre urban arts and creativity centre will host the &quot;Innovation Village&quot;. Here visitors can test future-oriented prototypes which have been specially developed with the support of the Cap Digital cluster and the Paris Region. Moreover, delegations from such major international cities as Tokyo, Brazil, Amsterdam, London, Vienna, Berlin, and Copenhagen will present their visionary and innovative digital services and technologies. International design competitions, digital installation and multi-media performances will complement this universal exhibition of the digital revolution. <strong>Don&#39;t forget to visit PICNIC and IIP Create at the Innovation Village as well</strong>!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please visit the Futur en Seine website for the <a href=\"http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/\" target=\"_blank\">full program</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>PICNIC&nbsp;website readers will receive a very special discount offer for all tickets to the festival.</strong> Please email Charlotte Sagnier (charlotte.sagnier[at]capdigital.com)&nbsp;for details about the discount.</p>\r\n','2011-06-14 18:36:28','2011-06-14 18:42:27','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-14 17:41:00',0,71,0,''),(109,15,'\'Best Scene in Town\' is back at PICNIC Festival!',NULL,'<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	This year the Mobile Design Challenge &#39;Best Scene in Town&#39; is back again at the PICNIC festival - bigger and better than ever!</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Best Scene in Town is a design challenge in which you designers from different disciplines compete to create the ultimate mobile experience. Students teams mixed(!) from leading learning institutions combine creative forces to design, present and pilot new ideas on how we can interact with locations and people using our smartphones.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Participating are:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Massachusetts Institute of Technology</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Hong Kong Design Institute</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Parsons - The New School for Design</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		University of Amsterdam</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		University of Applied Sciences, Amsterdam</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Utrecht University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	But we are open to have creative and enthusiastic students from other institutions join in as well. So check out the <a href=\"http://www.bestsceneintown.com/\" target=\"_blank\">website of 7Scenes</a> for more info on how to join the Challenge. And maybe you&#39;ll win a trip to PICNIC Festival 2011 in Amsterdam to build and test case your idea!</p>\r\n','2011-06-14 21:57:36','2011-06-21 07:38:00','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-14 21:57:36',0,72,0,''),(110,31,'Waag Society','','<p>\r\n	Waag Society, the institute for art, science and technology, develops creative technology for social innovation. The foundation researches, develops concepts, pilots and prototypes, and acts as an intermediate between the arts, science and the media.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Six years ago, Waag Society Director Marleen Stikker co-founded PICNIC, creating the leading innovation platform in Amsterdam.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	For more info visit: <a href=\"http://www.waag.org\" target=\"_blank\">www.waag.org</a></p>','2011-06-16 08:13:54','2011-06-22 15:31:25','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-16 08:13:00',0,76,30,'Waag Society'),(111,36,'Wired',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Wired</strong> is the magazine about what&rsquo;s next &ndash; bringing you the people, the trends and the big ideas that will change our lives. Each month, through thought-provoking features and stunning photography, we explore the next big ideas in science, culture, business &ndash; wherever innovation and new thinking are reshaping our world.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Since the US edition of Wired launched in 1993, the magazine has been synonymous with informed and intelligent analysis, and a consistently reliable predictor of change. The UK edition, launched in April 2009, is similarly committed to bringing you the best writers and photographers; compelling long-form journalism; extraordinary photography and design;and the people, products and ideas that matter.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Follow Wired <a href=\"http://www.wired.co.uk\" target=\"_blank\">online</a> and on <a href=\"http://twitter.com/#!/wireduk\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2011-06-16 08:24:21','2011-06-16 08:54:59','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-20 08:24:00',0,77,0,'Wired'),(113,1,'Office Manager',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Job Description: Office Manager </strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC has an exciting opportunity for the position of Office Manager. &nbsp;We are looking for a candidate able to begin 18 July 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	As the PICNIC Office Manager, you play a central role within the team. You ensure that everything in the office and for the team runs smoothly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Activities include the following:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	General support for the team</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		First point of contact for the organization</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Managing incoming phone calls, mail and emails and refer the inquiry to the right person / discipline</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Organizing meetings and appointments for team and board of PICNIC</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Managing the office (basic) IT and administration</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Ordering stationery and office supplies</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Taking minutes during team meetings</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Organizing the recruitment of new staff and setting up work environment</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Support the production department with general research and acquisition</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		&nbsp;Support the marketing department with mailings and invitations</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Relationship management with various suppliers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Requirements:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We are looking for a meticulous person, result- and deadline oriented, with good writing skills in Dutch and English. You should be a team player, experienced with the full Microsoft office package, and ideally possessing a clear interest in event production and the context of PICNIC in particular.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This position is an ideal opportunity for a (recent) graduate looking for a challenging experience in a dynamic office environment.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Description of PICNIC:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC is Europe&rsquo;s largest event for creativity and innovation, taking place every year in September in Amsterdam. It combines a high-level conference, open meetings, closed VIP events, award ceremonies, roundtable discussions, workshops, master classes, networking events, and top-class entertainment. PICNIC is a showcase for new products and services developed at the crossroads of business, media, science and the arts.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Please send your CV and letter of motivation in English to: Kitty Leering [kitty@picnicnetwork.org].</p>\r\n','2011-06-17 09:13:13','2011-06-20 07:39:33','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-20 09:30:00',0,NULL,5,'Jobs'),(115,15,'Look who\'s talking at PICNIC 2011','','<p>\r\n	PICNIC prides itself on bringing attention to some of the world&#39;s most innovative thinkers. Here&#39;s your chance to see and hear them before the rest of the world has discovered them!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We&#39;re just announcing this year&#39;s line-up. Here are just six of the people you&#39;ll have the chance to hear from and meet at PICNIC Festival 2011 and what you can expect from them:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/adam-greenfield\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Adam Greenfield</strong></a> brings&nbsp;critical thinking about how applied technology in the public space will never make the city smart, but should instead make its inhabitants smarter through human-centered (interaction) design.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/toby-barnes\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Toby Barnes</strong></a> brings&nbsp;inventive ways to open up the cities&#39; dynamics with visualisation and gamification.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/mark-woerde\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Mark Woerde</strong></a> brings&nbsp;insights in how to transform brands into meaningful pro-social brands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/eva-gladek\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Eva Gladek</strong></a> brings designs for closed ecosystems that provide the possibility for net-zero impact food production.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/peter-corbett\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Peter Corbett</strong></a> brings&nbsp;creative approaches on interactive marketing and a focus on civic innovation through community building.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/heath-bunting\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Heath Bunting</strong></a> brings his artist&#39;s vision&nbsp;to create a new (and legal!) identity for you, which you can actually purchase from him in neat, ready to use packages. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Browse their profiles and read about all of the speakers at PICNIC Festival 2011 in our <a href=\"http://www.picnicnetwork.org/picnic11-speakers\" target=\"_blank\">speakers gallery</a>. &nbsp;Be sure to check back for exciting new announcements throughout the summer.</p>\r\n','2011-06-20 13:43:35','2011-06-23 12:55:15','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-22 13:40:00',0,80,0,'2011 Speakers'),(116,15,'Share your green idea and win! ',NULL,'<p>\r\n	<strong>Enter the Postcode Lottery Green Challenge by 29 July</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	People from all over the world are signing up for the Postcode Lottery Green Challenge. So far, they have received entries from 52 different countries including Nepal, India, Sri Lanka, Kazakhstan, Nigeria, Russia, Belgium, Germany, Australia, the UK, the Netherlands and the USA. You can submit your idea or product at <a href=\"http://www.greenchallenge.info\">www.greenchallenge.info</a>.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The Postcode Lottery Green Challenge is looking for ideas that will contribute to a better, greener world. Dream up a greenhouse-gas-reducing product or service and send in your idea before 29 July. The entrant with the best idea will win &euro;500,000, expert coaching and help to bring his or her idea to market. The finalists will present their ideas and the prize winners will be revealed during PICNIC Festival 2011.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Put your green idea on Facebook for a chance to win an iPad 2</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Even those without a business plan can participate in the Green Challenge. Got a simple but brilliant idea? Share it in just two lines on the <a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/PostcodeLotteryGreenChallenge\" target=\"_blank\">Green Challenge Facebook</a> page. Green Challenge ambassador Richard Branson is calling on all Facebook visitors to think of a green idea, and share it with the world. The best one wins an iPad 2, a design eco-case and an iPad2 solar charger.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<strong>Past Green Challenge winner creates Mushroom Packaging for Dell Computers</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Check out the Green Challenge blog for green ideas in action, including the latest initiative from 2008 Green Challenge winner Eben Bayer. Find out more about his <a href=\"http://www.greenchallenge.info/MediaDetails/MushroomPackagingForDellComputers.htm\" target=\"_blank\">Mushroom Packaging for Dell Computers</a>.</p>\r\n','2011-06-22 20:53:10','2011-06-22 20:55:52','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-22 20:53:10',0,81,0,''),(117,39,'PICNIC Business Club',NULL,'<h2>\r\n	PICNIC Business Club is for companies like yours that want to&nbsp;get more out of their PICNIC experience.&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC&rsquo;s reach extends far beyond our yearly festival.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our strength lies in the people, opinions, knowledge and ideas we bring together.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Do you want to be sure you and your colleagues experience PICNIC to the fullest? Are you looking for a way formally associate your company with PICNIC? Do you want stronger connections to creative business leaders in Amsterdam and beyond? The PICNIC Business Club was created for you.</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Tap a network of inspiring individuals</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Besides tickets to the yearly festival, you&rsquo;ll join our inner circle and an intimate network of like-minded creative professionals, partners and advisors. Not to mention special benefits and events just for Business Club members.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	PICNIC Business Club membership packages are available for EUR 10,000. The membership is valid for one full year.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	PICNIC Business Club Benefits</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>10 Passe-partouts</strong> to PICNIC &lsquo;11 for you and your colleagues</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>40% off additional tickets</strong></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; An <strong>exclusive experience during PICNIC &rsquo;11</strong>, including access to the Business Club Lounge and a special side event just for Business Club members</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>Listing as a Business Club partner </strong>on the website at PICNIC &lsquo;11</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>Invitation to closed PICNIC partner events</strong> throughout the year for networking, brainstorming &amp; more</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&mdash; <strong>A fun and casual event</strong> just for Business Club members in spring 2012</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h5 class=\"article_intro\">\r\n	Want to find out more?</h5>\r\n<p>\r\n	Get in touch with us at infopicnicnetwork.org or call&nbsp;31 (0)20 320 5813 to find out how you can become&nbsp;a member of the PICNIC Business Club.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>','2011-06-23 14:17:48','2011-06-23 15:33:26','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-23 14:17:48',0,82,0,'Business Club'),(119,40,'CnB',NULL,'<p>\r\n	22-24 June 2011</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Cologne, Germany</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.c-o-pop.de/en/cnb-convention/home\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The three-day event invites experienced experts and startups, company founders and dedicated freelancers, creative people and business pros, university graduates and students, to discuss future formats for production, financing and exploitation, new life and business models, new trends and visions.&nbsp;</p>\r\n','2011-06-23 14:58:50','2011-06-23 15:04:29','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-23 14:58:50',0,NULL,0,'Creativity & Business Convention'),(120,40,'SXSW',NULL,'<p>\r\n	9-18 March 2012</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Austin, Texas</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.sxsw.com\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The South by Southwest (SXSW) Conferences &amp; Festivals offer the unique convergence of original music, independent films, and emerging technologies</p>\r\n','2011-06-23 15:03:16','2011-06-23 15:04:04','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-23 15:03:16',0,NULL,0,'SXSW'),(121,40,'Futur en Seine',NULL,'<p>\r\n	17-26 June 2011</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Paris, France</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.futur-en-seine.fr/en/\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This is the popular Festival of Life and Creativity, where the general public meets the innovative creative industries to imagine, build and celebrate the digital future together!</p>\r\n','2011-06-23 15:06:26','2011-06-23 15:06:26','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-23 15:06:26',0,NULL,0,'Futur en Seine'),(122,40,'NEXT11',NULL,'<p>\r\n	May 17-18, 2011</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Berlin, Germany</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://nextconf.eu/next11/\" target=\"_blank\">Website</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Business developers, marketing experts and agency managers are faced with the challenge to create new applications out of the ever-growing data stream with added value for the consumer. In our data-driven economy, the consumer is in the focus point of consideration. Because his behaviour determines who wins, what lasts and what will be sold. Data is the crucial driver to develop relevant products and services for the consumer.</p>\r\n','2011-06-23 15:08:16','2011-06-23 15:08:16','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-23 15:08:16',0,NULL,0,'NEXT11'),(123,36,'M/I/S/C/',NULL,'<p>\r\n	M/I/S/C/ is a quarterly magazine distributed globally about business innovation and design thinking. Organized around four key concepts: Movement / Intuition / Structure / Complexity /, it&#39;s a magazine about art. It&#39;s a magazine about design. It&#39;s a magazine about business. M/I/S/C/ is about pushing new creative territories and providing new perspectives on everything from strategic innovation to design thinking to social innovation to behavioral economics.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	http://miscology.com/</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 08:19:48','2011-06-27 08:19:48','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 08:19:48',0,83,0,'M/I/S/C/'),(124,41,'Virtueel Platform',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Virtueel Platform is the sector institute for e-culture in the Netherlands. Its mission is to stimulate and strengthen cultural innovation by sharing knowledge about e-culture and increasing its visibility and scope.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Virtueel Platform has three main strategic goals:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	- Track developments and stimulate research</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	- Give the sector&rsquo;s achievements national and international recognition</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	- Strengthen relationships between the sector and cultural/social/political organisations</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Virtueel Platform is particularly interested in reaching out to individuals and organisations working in the arts and culture sectors, the government, funding agencies, education and the creative industry.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	E-culture has two main aspects. In one&nbsp;sense, e-culture refers to electronic arts, network culture, media use and research into the cultural appropriation of new technologies. However, e-culture includes the much broader impact that digital technologies and interactive media currently have as the most important catalysts for change in the way we live, work and play. Meanwhile we should also remember that culture and the arts have always been at the basis of inspiring the developments in digital media. In short, e-culture is at the very cutting edge of all social and economic development.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Virtueel Platform is an independent foundation subsidised by the Ministry of Education, Culture and Science in the Netherlands.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.virtueelplatform.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:32:59','2011-06-27 10:44:25','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:32:59',0,85,0,'Virtueel Platform'),(125,41,'7Scenes',NULL,'<p>\r\n	7scenes is a mobile technology company, based in Amsterdam and founded in 2007. 7scenes has its roots in many years of research done at medialab Waag Society &amp; Just Objects and is used in many different fields like education, cultural heritage, tourism, events and entertainment. Both in The Netherlands and in many other parts of the world.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.7scenes.com</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:35:26','2011-06-27 10:42:45','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:35:26',0,NULL,0,'7Scenes'),(126,41,'Syntens',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Syntens&rsquo; mission is to strengthen the capacity to innovate of small and medium-sized companies, to stimulate successful innovation and to make a visible contribution towards sustainable growth.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our network can help strengthen your business by providing the right knowhow and resources, enabling you to innovate quicker and more efficiently. Syntens understands who and what you need to successfully create new business.&nbsp;&nbsp;If your motto is &#39;Things can always be improved&#39; and if you believe in the power of cooperation, then Syntens is here for you!</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.syntens.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:37:12','2011-06-27 10:48:25','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:37:12',0,86,0,'Syntens'),(127,41,'Non-fiction',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Non-fiction is an innovation agency reconfiguring popular engagement with public institutions for the 21st century. It was founded by Michiel van Iersel and Juha van &lsquo;t Zelfde in 2008.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We work for and with a growing number of public institutions, museums, universities, design agencies, artists, architects and musicians. Amongst them are the Stedelijk Museum, Bimhuis, Muziekgebouw aan &lsquo;t IJ, Museum De Paviljoens, Stadsherstel, North Sea Jazz, Netherlands Institute of Cultural Heritage, SNS REAAL Fonds and Michel van der Aa.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Through artistic, economic and social synthesis we design bespoke situations for collaborative experience of cutting-edge art, music, heritage and public space. These always happen both in real space and online, via ubiquitous digital networking technologies.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our office is situated in the former chemistry lab of the Netherlands Institute of Cultural Heritage, right in the middle of the Amsterdam&rsquo;s vibrant museum quarter at Museumplein.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://www.non-fiction.nl\" target=\"_blank\">www.non-fiction.nl</a></p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:40:04','2011-06-27 10:40:04','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:40:04',0,NULL,0,'Non-fiction'),(128,41,'Mediagilde',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Mediagilde (Media Guild) is a not for profit organization that fosters innovation and brings it to the market and to society. Mediagilde has two important goals that follow naturally from each other:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To support innovative starters in the creative industry</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		To bring businesses and knowledge institutes in touch with the creative industry and innovation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	Everybody who is talented and has a good (interactive media) idea can be considered for a place at Mediagilde. All you need is an entrepreneurial character and an excellent innovative idea that can potentially reach the market.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Mediagilde selects the best proposals and offers selected starters a completely equipped workspace. Like this, you (and your team) will have a dynamic creative environment to work in. All workspaces are&nbsp;equipped with excellent technical facilities such as glass fibre connections. Besides that, all starters participate in a extensive support program geared towards technological development, matter-of-fact business knowledge and entrepreneurship.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.mediaglide.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:53:01','2011-06-27 10:53:01','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:53:01',0,NULL,0,'Mediagilde'),(130,41,'Kenniskring',NULL,'<p>\r\n	need English text</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.kenniskring.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:54:26','2011-06-27 10:54:26','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:54:26',0,NULL,0,'Kenniskring'),(131,41,'European Journalism Centre',NULL,'<p>\r\n	The European Journalism Centre (EJC) is an independent, international, non-profit institute dedicated to the highest standards in journalism, primarily through the further training of journalists and media professionals. Building on its extensive international network, the Centre operates as a facilitator and partner in a wide variety of training projects.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The main goals of the EJC are to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		promote high quality journalism through professional training, particularly in a European context;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		provide a forum for discussion, debate, and exchanges of views and experience for journalists, editors, media executives and other media professionals;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		support, through training and networking, high standards of journalism in developing countries;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		promote further journalism training that answers the needs of media professionals and the media industry;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		monitor and reflect, via research, surveys and publications, on the present and future challenges facing the media;</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		create and support networks among media professionals within Europe and with other parts of the world.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	The EJC plays a unique role at the European level as a partner and organiser for media companies, professional organisations, journalism schools and governmental bodies seeking to establish activities and projects.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.ejc.com</p>','2011-06-27 10:55:45','2011-06-27 10:55:45','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:55:45',0,NULL,0,'European Journalism Centre'),(132,41,'Creative Cities Amsterdam Area',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Creative Amsterdam stimulates the creative industries in the seven cities of the Amsterdam Metropolitan Area. The programme was initiated in 2007, with a pledge to cooperate on the part of the region&rsquo;s local government and other organisations.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Creative Amsterdam offers national and international companies access to the creative potential of the region. Conversely, it also helps the region&rsquo;s creative companies find the right facilities&nbsp;to stimulate their entrepreneurialism.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The programme does this through three key activities:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Concentrating information and activities, by bringing them together in a single physical and digital location: www.creativeamsterdam.nl</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Facilitating, by improving services to foreign companies and to starting and growing entrepreneurs</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Promoting the creative industries in the region so that they attract national and international attention</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.ccaa.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 10:58:53','2011-06-27 10:58:53','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 10:58:53',0,NULL,0,'Creative Cities Amsterdam Area'),(133,41,'Amsterdam Innovation Motor',NULL,'<p>\r\n	Amsterdam Innovation Motor (AIM) was established to maintain and consolidate the trendsetting position of the Amsterdam region in the knowledge economy. AIM is directed by the Economic Development Board Amsterdam (EDBA).AIM promotes innovation, cooperation and new business in the Amsterdam region. To do so, we focus on the development of sectors that are the most promising in terms of strengthening the position of the region, namely:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Creative industries</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		ICT</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Life sciences</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Financial and Business Services</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n		Sustainability</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n	www.aimamsterdam.nl</p>\r\n','2011-06-27 11:01:03','2011-06-27 11:01:03','2035-01-01 00:00:00','2011-06-27 11:01:03',0,NULL,0,'Amsterdam Innovation Motor');
