INSERT INTO `shouts` VALUES (8,2,NULL,NULL,'What do people think of the first iteration of the Club area? What direction should we take?',0,'2011-05-18 16:52:40','2011-06-01 08:39:39','',NULL,NULL),(10,2,8,'Video','Check out this awesome video about explosives and art. My two  favourite subjects!',0,'2011-05-18 16:54:56','2011-05-25 22:29:10','',NULL,NULL),(13,4,NULL,NULL,'This is how I get my stuff done http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4P785j15Tzk',0,'2011-05-25 09:55:11','2011-06-07 20:32:43','',NULL,NULL),(14,2,9,'Video','Even a complex concept such as using Charlie plexing to drive multiple LEDs using only and digital outputs can be taught to a 10 year old boy using the Arduino. He\'s now bored with lessons at school though.',0,'2011-05-25 22:24:46','2011-05-25 22:32:46','',NULL,NULL),(15,2,1,'Link','Arduino is an open-source electronics prototyping platform based on flexible, easy-to-use hardware and software. It\'s intended for artists, designers, hobbyists, and anyone interested in creating interactive objects or environments.',0,'2011-05-25 22:34:21','2011-05-25 22:34:21','',NULL,NULL),(16,33,10,'Video','I dabble in documentary filmmaking. Here\'s one I made in Mississippi this year.',0,'2011-05-27 14:54:26','2011-06-11 00:23:10','',NULL,NULL),(17,46,NULL,NULL,'What defines a city? For me one of the things that does that is the rich visual culture you find on the streets in the form of posters. Obviously we have a big challenge, saying we’re building PICNIC City. Since it is for only three days, and we only have about a week to build it. To create a city-link atmosphere we started the PICNIC Poster Project. We’re inviting hand-picked leading designers and agencies in our international networks, to make artwork for us in the form of ‘posters’ (both vertical and horizontal for screen based applications). Posters we can use in several ways, from decoration on site (poster walls like in real cities, but then all related to PICNIC Festival), online as backgrounds for the website or announcing separate themes, workshops or speakers, for media and even the visual speaker announcements during the festival. This leads to a highly diverse and eclectic visual language that brings the city to life. We have started from the overarching theme ‘Urban Futures’, then narrow down to the main categories to people (speakers, presenters, etc.).\n\nAt this moment a variety of creatives is working on their contributions and we can’t wait to see the first results. If you create visually brilliant work yourself, feel free to contact me. Then you get a briefing on the subject that need visual support.',0,'2011-05-30 05:32:29','2011-05-30 05:32:29','',NULL,NULL),(18,11,2,'Link','Just read this really interesting article on the Doors of Perception weblog on world\'s stack of copper running out. And as copper is an essential factor for stashing green energy - from wind and sun for instance - this is another insightful example of how complex \"being green\" actually is. Read it and join our search for alternative green energy sources at PICNIC Festival 2011 in Amsterdam!',0,'2011-06-03 10:05:57','2011-06-14 06:53:06','',NULL,NULL),(19,43,3,'Link','All students out there, sign up for Best Scene in Town!! The ultimate challenge to create new mobile experiences in an international team. ',0,'2011-06-03 14:23:47','2011-06-03 14:23:47','',NULL,NULL),(20,4,11,'Video','Kuroshio Sea - 2nd largest aquarium tank in the world. I could stare at this all day!',0,'2011-06-03 16:27:51','2011-06-08 09:52:51','',NULL,NULL),(21,11,4,'Link','Only 6 more days to apply for the Vodafone Mobile Clicks Award! \nAre you an innovative, mobile internet start-up and do you want to have a go at some of the 225.000 euros (!!!) prize money? Than check out how you can submit your company for the Vodafone Mobile Clicks Contest! Here you can find more info and the conditions: http://developer.vodafone.com/mobileclicks2011/ \n\nAward ceremony at PICNIC Festival 2011 in Amsterdam. ',0,'2011-06-06 19:25:53','2011-06-06 19:25:53','',NULL,NULL),(22,11,NULL,NULL,'Tomorrow, Marcel (Creative Director PICNIC) and Alrik (Spatial designer) will present the latest PICNIC stuff. Marcel will tell more about the new website, the PICNIC Club and the upcoming PNN! And Alrik will present the blueprint of our PICNIC City!!!\n\nExciting......',0,'2011-06-07 19:28:30','2011-06-07 19:28:30','',NULL,NULL),(24,88,64,'Photo','First post... Trying it out.',0,'2011-06-07 22:19:09','2011-06-21 17:01:22','',NULL,NULL),(25,68,5,'Link','In Situated Technologies Pamphlets 8, Christian Nold and Rob van Kranenburg initiate a public debate about an Internet of Things in the public interest. Nold and Kranenburg propose tangible design interventions that challenge an internet dominated by commercial tools and systems, emphasizing that people from all walks of life have to be at the table when we talk about alternate possibilities for ubiquitous computing. Ultimately, the authors ask us to re-engage the creative capacities of digital platforms to live and politicize our troubled complicity.',0,'2011-06-08 07:57:13','2011-06-08 07:57:13','',NULL,NULL),(26,87,NULL,NULL,'Hey Joep, nice to have you here sitting on my blanket. Enjoy discovering and contributing! ',0,'2011-06-08 19:47:49','2011-06-14 14:17:44','Member',98,NULL),(28,87,7,'Link','There is good reason to think that the way we think about who is in our social networks is going to undergo massive change, driven in part by our new access to strangers with common interests. In a great post on TechCrunch in October 2010, Naval Ravikant and Adam Rifkin articulated the difference between the “social graph” (the network of people you know personally) and the “interest graph” (the network of people who share interests with you, but who you don’t necessarily know personally).',0,'2011-06-08 21:50:40','2011-06-08 21:50:40','',NULL,NULL),(29,87,8,'Link','Facebook is building a phone. Google is building a car. Apple is building a spaceship. Exploring innovation and megalomania in architecture it\'s one giant building that would hold 12,000 people. The building is circular with \"not a straight piece of glass\"--all curved. What are your thoughts?\n',0,'2011-06-08 22:10:46','2011-06-09 14:04:22','',NULL,NULL),(30,2,NULL,NULL,'Hi Fran. Just testing the \"post to somebody else\'s profile\" functionality. This message will only appear on your profile if somebody clicks on \"from others\" or you don\'t have anything posted on your profile from yourself.',0,'2011-06-09 10:51:46','2011-06-09 10:51:46','Member',87,NULL),(31,87,NULL,NULL,'Hey crazy! Nice having you on my blanket! How your doing? Will I see you in September? ',0,'2011-06-09 16:49:28','2011-06-09 16:49:28','Member',108,NULL),(32,87,NULL,NULL,'I was waiting for you, Bart! Haha, come and sit on my blanket! ',0,'2011-06-09 19:06:10','2011-06-09 19:06:10','Member',112,NULL),(33,112,9,'Link','In the spirit of the Cities theme:\n\nInteresting idea to balance things out in the parking lots by making the extremely popular ones more expensive and the less popular ones less expensive. And all that with a little help from your smartphone.',0,'2011-06-09 19:42:24','2011-06-09 19:42:24','',NULL,NULL),(34,87,NULL,NULL,'ahhhhhh nice to have you here! As I said, tell us what you think and the amazing guys from Yoomee will work their magic... hugs!',0,'2011-06-09 19:44:57','2011-06-09 19:44:57','Member',116,NULL),(35,125,NULL,NULL,'If you are an entrepreneur and want to come to Brazil to share ideas and do business with us, please contact me :)',0,'2011-06-09 20:59:59','2011-06-21 16:56:52','',NULL,NULL),(36,94,67,'Photo','Currently putting together the \'building blocks\' for PICNIC city...gathering a nice mix of sorts of S/M/L/XL mobile spaces >> if you know of (or have) unique units that can function as a space for a lab / workshop / lecture...drop me a line at alrik@picnicnetwork.org',0,'2011-06-10 07:02:03','2011-06-10 07:02:03','',NULL,NULL),(37,2,12,'Video','I\'ve just come across Bitcoin which is a digital currency based on Open Source technology. Unlike other digital currencies, Bitcoin avoids central authorities and issuers. I\'ve never heard of this before. Please enlighten me. Could this be the currency for the PICNIC city?',0,'2011-06-10 12:31:29','2011-06-10 12:31:29','',NULL,NULL),(38,87,68,'Photo','Hey beautiful, welcome to the PICNIC! Let\'s go crazy next week and have some food, wine and Frozzzzzzzzzzz!',0,'2011-06-10 16:03:51','2011-06-17 21:50:28','Member',132,NULL),(41,108,11,'Link','Amongst the hats I wear is that of the Chair of Trustees of Cockpit Arts an award winning business incubator for designer makers. I am excited that the event is being held at NDSM since they also appear to have incubator spaces - do you think there would be any merit in putting us together in some way on the programme at PICNIC as examplars of best practice in the field ? I hope so ! \n',0,'2011-06-10 23:52:36','2011-06-18 23:25:11','',NULL,NULL),(42,139,NULL,NULL,'Advertisers do have sustainable outdoor media choices that better align with their sustainable ambitions then traditional forms of outdoor advertising',0,'2011-06-11 06:45:29','2011-06-11 06:45:29','',NULL,NULL),(43,139,NULL,NULL,'Looking to meet others who are using their businesses to foster positive change. I believe business will drive sustainability not the government and unfortunately not individuals. Profits are still driving sustainability and profits with principles are becoming more important to brands who are authentically making sustainability a core part of their business strategies. I do have faith in the world of business but we do need to redefine how we define success. Money talks but it is not the only factor that makes a business successful',0,'2011-06-11 07:19:33','2011-06-14 01:58:21','',NULL,NULL),(45,112,13,'Video','Page One seems to be a very interesting documentary about a year inside the The New York Times. About traditional media, partially being taken over by new media, about a loss of power in traditional media, etc. Really interesting, would love to see it!\n',0,'2011-06-11 14:53:36','2011-06-11 14:53:36','',NULL,NULL),(46,139,NULL,NULL,'Prosocial advertising is a new term to me but one that fits perfectly with the ambitions of GreenGraffiti. Mark Woerde has published a book, \"How will advertising heal the world and your business\" available for free at this link where you can down load it for free  http://www.letsheal.org/ \nThanks Franziska for sending me this link! My blanket is already paying off at Picnic!',0,'2011-06-12 07:42:10','2011-06-12 07:42:10','',NULL,NULL),(47,139,NULL,NULL,'Not to be blatantly tooting our own horns but I just saw this community action that our Italian partners did. This is what GreenGraffiti® is all about, using new media, social media and the community to make a statement. \nThe Italians go to the poles this week and sustainability is not something the current government is supporting so the people have taken their message to the streets!\nhttp://vimeo.com/24761851 ',0,'2011-06-12 10:57:32','2011-06-12 10:57:32','',NULL,NULL),(48,139,14,'Video','',0,'2011-06-12 10:58:32','2011-06-12 10:58:32','',NULL,NULL),(49,87,15,'Video','Love the new Greenpeace Campaign - Facebook: Unfriend coal ',0,'2011-06-12 12:46:12','2011-06-12 12:46:12','',NULL,NULL),(50,108,13,'Link','Architecture seems to be one of the important themes of this year\'s PICNIC . The artist Pablo Bronstein explores this in his new show just opened at the Institiute of Contemporary Arts in London . Check it out and if you are in London it really is worth a visit. Let me know and I might even come with you ! ',0,'2011-06-13 07:34:09','2011-06-13 07:34:09','',NULL,NULL),(51,182,NULL,NULL,'I am an idea generator inspired by people\'s creativity and current need for transformation',0,'2011-06-13 11:53:54','2011-06-21 21:45:50','',NULL,NULL),(52,87,16,'Video','... and another one in the row of creative ads for a good cause... ',0,'2011-06-13 12:01:35','2011-06-13 12:01:35','',NULL,NULL),(53,126,14,'Link','Last time I was in Amsterdam was 2000 for the Doors of Perception conference which was a very inspiring conference. Am really looking forward to returning to Amsterdam for the Picnic Festival. ',0,'2011-06-14 06:33:21','2011-06-14 06:33:21','',NULL,NULL),(55,126,70,'Photo','When working at Nokia in London we had a Jamon Picnic. I also bring jamon cutting skills... if anyone needs',0,'2011-06-14 06:50:54','2011-06-20 05:06:13','',NULL,NULL),(56,108,NULL,NULL,'I am curious , good ( mostly ) and love Brownies !',0,'2011-06-14 13:26:00','2011-06-14 13:26:00','Member',76,NULL),(57,195,NULL,NULL,'Social media for schools has finally arrived! Free, private and incredibly easy to use for pupils/students, parents and teachers. Get to know each other, keep in touch and stay involved.',0,'2011-06-14 14:06:05','2011-06-14 14:06:05','',NULL,NULL),(58,195,NULL,NULL,'Did anyone remember to bring muffins to this PICNIC?',0,'2011-06-14 14:06:35','2011-06-20 08:20:55','',NULL,NULL),(59,108,NULL,NULL,'Are you actually coming to PICNIC ? .... and how do you know Dan Douglas ? Get him to come too !',0,'2011-06-14 23:00:01','2011-06-14 23:00:01','Member',198,NULL),(60,108,NULL,NULL,'What\'s for dinner ? So looking forward to PICNIC again this year ... love the new PICNIC Club Network ... so much more interactive than the old one and , for those who use it , it should add great value to the event.',0,'2011-06-14 23:20:27','2011-06-14 23:20:27','Member',36,NULL),(61,108,NULL,NULL,'You bring the Corkscrews ? I thought screw caps were greener !',0,'2011-06-15 13:56:20','2011-06-15 13:56:20','Member',204,NULL),(62,87,78,'Photo','Love the Musée du quai Branly in Paris for its green wall. The building was designed by architect Jean Nouvel. The \"green wall\" (200m long by 12m high) on part of the exterior of the museum was designed and planted by Gilles Clément and Patrick Blanc.',0,'2011-06-17 18:39:56','2011-06-17 18:39:56','',NULL,NULL),(63,112,16,'Link','Seems Nato is using Twitter in the bombardments in Libya. We should\'ve had Twitter before, so bombardments cause less civilian casualties...',0,'2011-06-17 18:47:47','2011-06-17 18:47:47','',NULL,NULL),(64,108,NULL,NULL,'Hi ! Tell me something about you . I look forward to meeting you at Picnic.',0,'2011-06-18 17:37:43','2011-06-18 17:37:43','Member',226,NULL),(65,108,NULL,NULL,'Hi Eric , Tell me something about yourself. I look forward to meeting you at Picnic ! ',0,'2011-06-18 17:39:54','2011-06-18 17:39:54','Member',227,NULL),(66,108,NULL,NULL,'Skydiving ! Blimey ... Hope you don\'t miss my blanket !',0,'2011-06-18 17:54:43','2011-06-18 17:54:43','Member',62,NULL),(67,11,17,'Link','What about this for camping? Get rid of your traditional tent and start using the Cristal Bubble by Pierre Stephane Duma: a transparant bubble with 360 degree view on your environment (and vice versa, so you shouldn\'t have an issue with privacy ;-)',0,'2011-06-19 17:51:44','2011-06-19 17:51:44','',NULL,NULL),(68,247,NULL,NULL,'Stimulate freedom of movement, to help people with jobs and accommodation anywhere,with smarter apps. ',0,'2011-06-23 13:57:35','2011-06-23 13:57:35','',NULL,NULL),(69,247,NULL,NULL,'To predict the future, invest in the young generation to control a successful world.',0,'2011-06-23 14:56:11','2011-06-23 14:56:11','',NULL,NULL),(70,247,NULL,NULL,'Many countries cut in costs for education budgets, the essence of using less government money for a higher education performance, is attracting companies to invest in students to get trough college and university education. ',0,'2011-06-23 19:10:04','2011-06-23 19:10:04','',NULL,NULL),(71,108,NULL,NULL,'You bring the dancing , I bring the dance-floor , Laurelene brings the tunes and Arne can mash us all up nicely together ! ... and maybe we can find a way to do it so Dance4Life benefits ?',0,'2011-06-24 15:36:17','2011-06-24 15:36:17','Member',260,NULL),(72,108,NULL,NULL,'Yay ! ... at last somebody on the network who has actually bought a ticket .... a veritable early bird ! ! ',0,'2011-06-24 15:55:10','2011-06-24 15:55:10','Member',259,NULL),(78,108,NULL,NULL,'Hi Rosalyn , Are you actually coming to Picnic ? Sit on my blanket so we can talk about creative incubators !',0,'2011-06-24 16:01:04','2011-06-24 16:01:04','Member',257,NULL),(79,247,NULL,NULL,'In order to create services on a transnational scale, people need to share more ideas to each other for effective collaboration. Look what the brothers Winklevoss brought to Mark Zuckerberg.  ',0,'2011-06-25 12:17:44','2011-06-25 12:17:44','',NULL,NULL),(80,2,NULL,NULL,'Next week we\'ll be working on the next iteration of the PICNIC club website, and taking onboard feedback so far. So watch this space...',0,'2011-06-28 08:59:50','2011-06-28 08:59:50','',NULL,NULL),(81,276,18,'Link','the future of publishing: transmedia and crossmedia.',0,'2011-06-28 09:58:38','2011-06-28 09:58:38','',NULL,NULL),(82,325,19,'Link','',1,'2011-06-28 14:57:48','2011-06-28 14:57:48','',NULL,NULL),(83,350,87,'Photo','Rich in Dollars & Senses',1,'2011-06-28 15:22:37','2011-06-28 15:22:37','',NULL,NULL),(84,11,20,'Link','Do you have innovative products and services that you want to show to our PICNIC Festival visitor? Than apply for a place at the PICNIC Market Place hosted by Chamber of Commerce and Syntens!',1,'2011-06-28 15:30:56','2011-06-28 15:30:56','',NULL,NULL);
