INSERT INTO `wall_posts` VALUES (3,33,8,'I didn\'t really notice the tags/themes to the far right... Also maybe restrict themes to a pulldown menu?','2011-05-20 08:35:44','2011-05-20 08:35:44'),(4,2,8,'Hi Todd. Please ignore this! Just testing! Also, the Club area is about to change a lot today based in feedback from Marcel. Also the emails you get will look a lot better.','2011-05-20 08:37:37','2011-05-20 08:37:37'),(5,33,8,'No problem. I\'m just testing too! But will get out of here now then...','2011-05-20 08:39:24','2011-05-20 08:39:24'),(6,2,8,'Things will change a lot here by the end of today. Thanks for playing!','2011-05-20 08:59:09','2011-05-20 08:59:09'),(7,7,13,'Love it','2011-05-25 15:46:50','2011-05-25 15:46:50'),(8,5,13,'Haha brilliant!','2011-05-26 08:54:32','2011-05-26 08:54:32'),(9,2,16,'Todd that\'s awesome. I had no idea you did this kinda stuff. Very inspiring.','2011-06-01 20:28:05','2011-06-01 20:28:05'),(10,2,20,'Stop staring and get your stuff done! ;)','2011-06-03 18:58:27','2011-06-03 18:58:27'),(11,11,13,'LOL!!','2011-06-07 20:32:42','2011-06-07 20:32:42'),(12,11,20,'thank you Rich. Completely Zen again after watching this. \nBTW, what is the biggest tank in the world?','2011-06-07 20:38:13','2011-06-07 20:38:13'),(13,2,24,'Works fine... :-)','2011-06-07 22:21:07','2011-06-07 22:21:07'),(14,4,20,'Glad it chilled you out Kitty! Apparently the largest tank in the world is in Atlanta, Georgia, according to this blog post http://www.touropia.com/largest-aquariums-in-the-world/','2011-06-08 09:52:51','2011-06-08 09:52:51'),(15,98,26,'Hi Franziska, I was lucky there was still a free spot on your blanket. Cup of tea?  ','2011-06-08 19:56:07','2011-06-08 19:56:07'),(16,87,26,'always ;) reminder: need to buy a bigger blanket! ;)','2011-06-08 21:57:19','2011-06-08 21:57:19'),(17,87,30,'that\'s nice!','2011-06-09 11:06:59','2011-06-09 11:06:59'),(18,108,29,'Nowhere to hide !','2011-06-09 14:04:22','2011-06-09 14:04:22'),(19,108,31,'You sure will - already ticketed and ready to help you in any way. Can you fix it for me to say hello to the latest bunch of Knowmads? I am already plotting with Arne Hendriks to build a dance floor BarrysLounge stylee !','2011-06-10 15:50:05','2011-06-10 15:50:05'),(20,87,31,'will do, will do! can\'t wait to dance with you! but who is Arne Hendriks? (did I miss something??)','2011-06-10 16:06:51','2011-06-10 16:06:51'),(21,108,31,'I\'ll introduce you on Facebook then you can find out for yourself ... are you planning any visits to London before PICNIC ... Hope so ! Sx','2011-06-10 23:42:58','2011-06-10 23:42:58'),(22,33,16,'Thanks Andy. It was an amazing experience.','2011-06-11 00:23:09','2011-06-11 00:23:09'),(23,132,38,'Good idea!!! On your blanket?','2011-06-11 08:42:34','2011-06-11 08:42:34'),(24,87,43,'Hey Jim, nice meeting you and having you on my blanket. I love what you are writing here and just want to make you aware of \"How Advertising Will Heal the World and Your Business\" by Lemz\'s Mark Woerde. Don\'t know if you know the book already but if not, have a look and download it (for free) via http://www.letsheal.org/ If yes, nevermind... ','2011-06-11 09:02:16','2011-06-11 09:02:16'),(25,139,43,'Hi Franziska,\nThanks so much for this insight. I have just downloaded the book and will spend a few quiet hours reading it. Great to see that others share the opinion that advertising can be a solution and not just a necessary evil. Picnic is already working for me. THANK YOU!!!','2011-06-11 09:27:04','2011-06-11 09:27:04'),(26,108,51,'Come to Picnic and inspire others like you have inspired me !','2011-06-13 22:29:18','2011-06-13 22:29:18'),(27,126,43,'Hi Jim. For a perspective on things south of the equator, you should check out two Sydney companies run by friends of mine: Digital Eskimo and the Republic of Everyone. They are both heavily involved in sustainable communications, ROE are more advertising based, whereas DE are more into service and interaction design. ','2011-06-14 01:58:21','2011-06-14 01:58:21'),(28,139,43,'Thanks so much for the tip Kimberley. I will have a look at their companies. Greatly appreciated.','2011-06-14 06:00:08','2011-06-14 06:00:08'),(29,126,18,'I went to the Doors conference in 2000 and loved it. I saw lots of parallels when reading about Picnic: a wide variety of thought makers, future-focussed, sustainably thinking, multi-disciplinary, world improving.... ','2011-06-14 06:53:06','2011-06-14 06:53:06'),(30,108,55,'When were you at Nokia ? Do you know the fabulous Pria ? Should we get her along to PICNIC ?','2011-06-14 13:15:56','2011-06-14 13:15:56'),(31,108,26,'Until Franziska gets a bigger blanket ... come and sit on mine !','2011-06-14 14:17:43','2011-06-14 14:17:43'),(32,108,35,'Are you coming to PICNIC to share ideas with us ? Hope so !','2011-06-14 14:36:37','2011-06-14 14:36:37'),(33,198,59,'Hello, Sydney! Yes I am planning on actually going, though i\'ve not got my ticket yet. Dan Douglas I used to work with at de-construct. I\'ll give him a prod, see if he\'s around. How do you know the Douglas?','2011-06-14 23:12:36','2011-06-14 23:12:36'),(34,108,59,'I know all the best people ! He knows all the best accountants !','2011-06-14 23:16:52','2011-06-14 23:16:52'),(35,204,61,'Sorry to be a pedant, but actually cork is much greener. It\'s a secondary forestry product, and the cork forests of southern spain / portugal are the last habitat of the incredibly endangered Iberian Lynx, the only big cat native to Europe. There\'s an argument that screw caps improve the taste, but its a personal thing. \n\nhttp://www.livepositivelycollective.com/dynamic/live_positively/weve-been-inspired-by-put-a-cork-in-it/','2011-06-15 14:22:17','2011-06-15 14:22:17'),(36,108,61,'You\'re not a pedant ! It\'s to learn stuff like that is why I go to Picnic !I\'ll bring two bottles and we will compare and contrast !','2011-06-15 15:28:16','2011-06-15 15:28:16'),(37,108,38,'Hi Maartje , I am so looking forward to Picnic and do hope I will see you there ... You are of course always welcome on my blanket ! S x','2011-06-17 21:50:28','2011-06-17 21:50:28'),(38,108,62,'Very beautiful ... but here is a green wall with a purpose \nhttp://www.guardian.co.uk/global-development/2011/feb/25/great-green-wall-sahel-desertification','2011-06-17 22:34:08','2011-06-17 22:34:08'),(39,87,41,'Syd, this is a cool initiative. Want to know more!! We need a Skype call! Pronto!','2011-06-18 23:25:10','2011-06-18 23:25:10'),(40,108,67,'So will this be an option for accommodation at this year\'s Picnic? Hope so !','2011-06-19 22:37:37','2011-06-19 22:37:37'),(41,126,55,'Yes, I know the fabulous Pria. She was doing some excellent work there. Yes, she should definitely come along to Picnic. ','2011-06-20 05:06:13','2011-06-20 05:06:13'),(42,108,55,'On the case !','2011-06-20 06:03:27','2011-06-20 06:03:27'),(43,11,67,'haha, me too. But it is a bit pricy.... ','2011-06-20 08:18:08','2011-06-20 08:18:08'),(44,11,58,'Should check with our PR&Communications manager Liz Keel! Her self baked muffins are divine.......','2011-06-20 08:20:55','2011-06-20 08:20:55'),(45,239,35,'Im from brazil too. i love to share ideas in picnic with you.','2011-06-21 16:56:51','2011-06-21 16:56:51'),(46,239,24,'Works in brazil too, lol.','2011-06-21 17:01:21','2011-06-21 17:01:21'),(47,108,51,'Yay ! You\'re coming ! ','2011-06-21 21:45:50','2011-06-21 21:45:50'),(48,259,72,'i\'m all about the worms...','2011-06-24 15:57:04','2011-06-24 15:57:04'),(49,108,72,'Must have something to do with Dan D ... get him along too !','2011-06-24 16:26:04','2011-06-24 16:26:04'),(50,350,78,'Looking for Collaborators world-wide .....','2011-06-28 15:24:38','2011-06-28 15:24:38');
